Reasoning: 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control): The paper focuses on analyzing attacks in distributed control systems and designing more resilient control protocols. This falls under the scope of systems and control.
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security): The paper discusses cyber-physical attacks and increasing system awareness against attacks, which falls under the scope of cryptography and security.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence): The paper mentions designing novel control protocols to mitigate attacks, which could involve the use of AI techniques.
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture): The paper discusses the communication capabilities of compromised agents in distributed multi-agent systems, which falls under the scope of networking and internet architecture.
- cs.SE (Software Engineering): The paper may involve designing and implementing software for control protocols to mitigate attacks.
